modules.description: Provides functions to define commands with customizable completions and associated actions, enabling interactive user input handling. Works with command structures, completion generators, and action handlers. Used to build command-line interfaces with dynamic tab completion, such as in custom REPLs or configuration tools.

Provides command composition and evaluation with support for integer, float, string, and enumerated arguments. Enables building interactive command-line interfaces with argument parsing, completion, and help generation. Used to define and execute commands like `showf` and `add` with specified parameter types and documentation.
